//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_depot_levy}

NOTE: This operation creates an
{rbtgi_depot}
- a cohesive unit of Recipe Bottle infrastructure including the depot project, build bucket, container repository, Mason service account, and private worker pool
that share their productive lifecycle.

The
{rbtr_payor}
creates a new depot infrastructure from the
{rbtgi_payor_project}:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtgi_depot}
. *Depot Name*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»` provided as first argument
.. Validate depot name: lowercase letters, numbers, hyphens only, max 20 chars

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_payor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_payor_authenticate}

//axhos_step
. *Generate Depot Project ID*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TIMESTAMP»` as current time in YYYYMMDDHHmm format
.. Generate project ID: `rbw-«INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»-«TIMESTAMP»`
.. {rbbc_store}
as `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_require}
total length ≤ 30 characters

//axhos_step
. *Create Depot Project*:
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/create[projects.create] with:
... projectId: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... displayName: `RB Depot: «INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»`
... parent: `{rbrp_parent_type}s/{rbrp_parent_id}` (if parent_type != `none`)
.. {rbbc_await}
returned operation
.. {rbbc_require}
project creation successful

//axhos_step
. *Link Billing Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/billing/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects/updateBillingInfo[cloudbilling.projects.updateBillingInfo] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. Set billingAccountName: `billingAccounts/{rbrp_billing_account_id}`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response confirming billing linkage

//axhos_step
. *Get Depot Project Number*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/get[projects.get] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PROJECT_NUMBER»` from `.name` field (CRM v3 returns `projects/{number}`)
.. {rbbc_require}
valid numeric project number after extracting from name

//axhos_step
. *Enable Depot Project APIs*:
.. For each service in [`artifactregistry`, `cloudbuild`, `containeranalysis`, `iam`, `serviceusage`, `storage`]:
... Execute
{rbtoe_api_enable}
with service name and `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_require}
all APIs enabled successfully

//axhos_step
. *Create Private Worker Pool*:
.. Construct pool ID: `rbw-«INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»-pool`
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.workerPools/create[workerPools.create] with:
... parent: `projects/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/locations/{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... workerPoolId: `rbw-«INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»-pool`
... body:
+
----
{
  "privatePoolV1Config": {
    "workerConfig": {
      "machineType": "«RBRR_GCB_MACHINE_TYPE»"
    }
  }
}
----
.. {rbbc_store}
`«WORKER_POOL_STEM»` as base pool name (without project/region path prefix):
`rbw-«INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»-pool`
.. NOTE:
{rbrr_gcb_machine_type}
is a Compute Engine machine type (e.g., `e2-standard-2`), consumed at pool creation time.
Pool scales to zero workers when idle — no idle cost accrues.
.. Treat HTTP 409 CONFLICT as success (pool already exists — idempotent)

//axhos_step
. *Verify IAM Propagation*:
.. NOTE: After API enablement, IAM permissions may not be immediately available due to eventual consistency.
.. {rbbc_poll}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/list[artifactregistry.repositories.list] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` in `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
.. Poll at `RBGC_EVENTUAL_CONSISTENCY_SEC` intervals until HTTP 200 or `RBGC_MAX_CONSISTENCY_SEC` timeout
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response confirming IAM propagation complete
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if timeout: "IAM propagation timeout - artifactregistry API not accessible"

//axhos_step
. *Create Build Bucket*:
.. Construct bucket name: `rbw-«INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»-bucket`
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/json_api/v1/buckets/insert[storage.buckets.insert] with:
... name: `rbw-«INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»-bucket`
... location: `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... project: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... lifecycle rule: delete objects after 1 day
.. {rbbc_store}
`«BUILD_BUCKET»` as created bucket name

//axhos_step
. *Create Container Repository*:
.. Construct repository name: `rbw-«INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»-repository`
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/create[artifactregistry.repositories.create] with:
... repositoryId: `rbw-«INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»-repository`
... format: `DOCKER`
... location: `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... parent: `projects/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/locations/{rbrr_gcp_region}`
.. {rbbc_await}
returned operation
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»` as created repository name

//axhos_step
. *Create
{rbtr_mason}
Service Account*:
.. NOTE: The
{rbtr_mason}
replaces Cloud Build's implicit service account to provide deterministic permissions and predictable authorization within the depot infrastructure.
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create] with:
... accountId: `mason-«INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»`
... displayName: `Mason for RB Depot: «INPUT_DEPOT_NAME»`
... project: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«MASON_EMAIL»` from response `.email` field

//axhos_step
. *Configure
{rbtr_mason}
Permissions*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_repo} on `«GAR_REPOSITORY»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.writer`
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_bucket} on `«BUILD_BUCKET»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/storage.objectViewer`
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_project} on `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/viewer`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/logging.logWriter`

//axhos_step
. *Enable Cloud Build service agent to impersonate
{rbtr_mason}*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_sa} on `«MASON_EMAIL»`
.. Add member: `serviceAccount:service-«PROJECT_NUMBER»@gcp-sa-cloudbuild.iam.gserviceaccount.com`
.. Grant role: `roles/iam.serviceAccountTokenCreator`
.. NOTE: Cloud Build service agent is Google-provisioned (auto-created when Cloud Build API is enabled), not a user-created service account. The `tokenCreator` role enables build steps running as {rbtr_mason} (via the build JSON's `serviceAccount` field) to generate fresh access tokens for GCP API calls — required for GAR authentication (docker login, crane push). This is distinct from `serviceAccountUser` (actAs), which the {rbtr_director} holds on {rbtr_mason} for submitting builds.
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM binding successful

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_depot}
. *Display Depot Configuration*:
.. {rbbc_show}
depot creation successful
.. {rbbc_show}
required RBRR configuration values:
... `RBRR_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID=«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... `RBRR_GCP_REGION={rbrr_gcp_region}`
... `RBRR_GAR_REPOSITORY=«GAR_REPOSITORY»`
... `RBRR_GCB_POOL_STEM=«WORKER_POOL_STEM»`
.. {rbbc_show}
Mason service account: `«MASON_EMAIL»`

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_depot}
. *Update Depot Tracking*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_depot_list_update}
to refresh depot project tracking

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution creates depot infrastructure with configured build bucket, container repository, Mason service account, and private worker pool.
Proceed to
{rbtgo_governor_mantle}
to create the
{rbtr_governor}
for this depot.

{gcp_service}
operations.

[[rbrr_regime]]
//axvr_regime axf_bash axrd_file_sourced axrd_singleton
{rbrr_regime}::
Repository-wide configuration and installation-wide settings shared across all
{at_recipe_bottle}
operations.

[[rbrr_depot_project_id]]
//axl_voices axrg_variable axtg_project_id
{rbrr_depot_project_id}::
{gcp_service}
{gcp_project_id}
where all
{at_recipe_bottle}
resources are created and managed.

[[rbrr_gcp_region]]
//axl_voices axrg_variable axtg_region
{rbrr_gcp_region}::
Default
{gcp_service}
region for regional services like
{gar_service}
and
{gcb_service}.

[[rbrr_gar_repository]]
//axl_voices axrg_variable axtg_project_id
{rbrr_gar_repository}::
{gar_service}
{rbtgi_repository}
within
{rbrr_depot_project_id}
for
{at_bottle_image_s}
and
{rbtgi_metadata_s}.

[[rbrr_secrets_dir]]
//axl_voices axrg_variable axtu_path
{rbrr_secrets_dir}::
Directory containing service account credential files for all operational roles.
Validated to exist before credential file paths are derived.

[[rbrr_retriever_rbra_file]]
//axl_voices axrd_constructed axtu_path
{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file}::
Path to the
{rbtr_retriever}
{rbtgi_rbra_file}
for container image operations.
Derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `retriever/rbra.env`.

[[rbrr_director_rbra_file]]
//axl_voices axrd_constructed axtu_path
{rbrr_director_rbra_file}::
Path to the
{rbtr_director}
{rbtgi_rbra_file}
for build submission and image management.
Derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `director/rbra.env`.

[[rbrr_governor_rbra_file]]
//axl_voices axrd_constructed axtu_path
{rbrr_governor_rbra_file}::
Path to the
{rbtr_governor}
{rbtgi_rbra_file}
for
{gcp_project_id}
administration.
Derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `governor/rbra.env`.

[[rbrr_payor_rbro_file]]
//axl_voices axrd_constructed axtu_path
{rbrr_payor_rbro_file}::
Path to the
{rbtr_payor}
{rbro_regime}
credentials file for OAuth operations.
Derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `payor/rbro.env`.

[[rbrr_bottle_workspace]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_path
{rbrr_bottle_workspace}::
Container-internal working directory path for all
{at_bottle_container_s}.
Conventionally `/workspace`, following the industry-standard devcontainer convention.
Used by compose `working_dir`, volume mount targets, and bottle engagement tabtargets.

[[rbrr_vessel_dir]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_path
{rbrr_vessel_dir}::
Directory containing vessel configuration subdirectories for
{rbrr_regime}.

[[rbrr_dns_server]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_ipv4
{rbrr_dns_server}::
DNS server IP address for sentry container name resolution.

[[rbrm_ignite_machine_name]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_xname
{rbrm_ignite_machine_name}::
Podman machine name for bottle ignition operations.

[[rbrm_deploy_machine_name]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_xname
{rbrm_deploy_machine_name}::
Podman machine name for bottle deployment operations.

[[rbrm_crane_tar_gz]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_path
{rbrm_crane_tar_gz}::
Path to crane tool tarball for OCI registry operations.

[[rbrm_manifest_platforms]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_platform_list
{rbrm_manifest_platforms}::
Space-separated target platforms for multi-platform manifest creation.

[[rbrm_chosen_podman_version]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_version
{rbrm_chosen_podman_version}::
Podman version string for VM provisioning.

[[rbrm_chosen_vmimage_origin]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_string
{rbrm_chosen_vmimage_origin}::
Podman VM image origin specification.

[[rbrm_chosen_identity]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_string
{rbrm_chosen_identity}::
Identity specification for VM or build environment.

[[rbrr_gcb_machine_type]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_string
{rbrr_gcb_machine_type}::
Compute Engine machine type for the private worker pool, consumed at pool creation time by
{rbtgo_depot_levy}.
Default: `e2-standard-2`.
The pool resource holds this value; individual build requests do not specify machine type.

[[rbrr_gcb_pool_stem]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_string
{rbrr_gcb_pool_stem}::
Worker pool base name (suffixed with -tether/-airgap by derived constants).
Derived constants `RBDC_POOL_TETHER` and `RBDC_POOL_AIRGAP` expand this stem into full resource paths.
Must be set to the pool base name created by
{rbtgo_depot_levy}
for this depot.
Builds always use a private pool; the default shared pool is not supported.
`options.machineType` is omitted from the build JSON — machine type is a property of the pool resource.

NOTE: *Private pool is always required.*
Private pools are a prerequisite for VPC Service Controls and `NO_PUBLIC_EGRESS` hardening (see `RBSCB-CloudBuildPosture.adoc`).
Pricing is region-dependent: in us-central1/us-east4, private pool e2-standard-2 matches the default pool rate ($0.006/build-minute); in other regions the private pool rate is up to 1.4× higher.
This cost is accepted because the security prerequisite is non-negotiable and maintaining two code paths (conditional pool vs. default) doubles configuration surface.
+
Cloud Build supports two distinct machine type naming systems:
the default shared pool uses Cloud Build enum values (`E2_HIGHCPU_8`, `N1_HIGHCPU_32`) in `options.machineType` of the build JSON;
private pools use Compute Engine instance type names (`e2-standard-2`, `n2d-standard-4`, `c3-standard-8`) in `workerConfig.machineType` at pool creation.
Valid private pool families: `e2`, `n2d`, `c3` (availability varies by region).
Since Recipe Bottle uses only private pools, only the Compute Engine format is valid for
{rbrr_gcb_machine_type}.

[[rbrr_gcb_min_concurrent_builds]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_integer
{rbrr_gcb_min_concurrent_builds}::
Minimum concurrent Cloud Build execution count.

[[rbrr_gcb_timeout]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_duration
{rbrr_gcb_timeout}::
Maximum duration for Cloud Build operations.

[[rbrr_public_docs_url]]
//axvr_variable axd_required rbst_url
{rbrr_public_docs_url}::
Public docs URL — readme target for buh_tlt glossary links, updated per-release or per-incorporation.

// RBRG variable definitions eliminated (₣Av) — reliquaries replace pin-based tool image management
// Tool images (gcloud, docker, alpine, syft, binfmt, skopeo) now sourced from reliquary at conjure time

[[rbrr_group_public_docs]]
//axvr_group
{rbrr_group_public_docs}::
Public documentation URL for user-facing references.

